        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 3 at 8:14AM CDT until July 3 at 10:30AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast Oklahoma, including the following
counties, Latimer and Pittsburg.

* WHEN...Until 1030 AM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Some low-water crossings may become impassable.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 814 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly in the advisory area. Estimates between 0.5 and 2
inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch and locally higher
are expected over the area. This additional rain will result
in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Mcalester...                       Hartshorne...
Krebs...                           Kiowa...
Savanna...                         Alderson...
Ashland...                         Blanco...
Mcalester Regional Airport...      Higgins...
Haywood...                         Damon...
Yanush...                          Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                       Bache...
Dow...                             Gowen...
Arpelar...
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
